## SkroogeJsonParser — Generally Solid

### 1. **Keyword-based category type inference** (lines 663-684)

The `inferCategoryTypes()` method uses hardcoded French/English/Italian/Spanish keywords to determine Income vs Expense. While comprehensive, this is language-biased. A user with categories named in a different language (e.g., Japanese, Russian, Arabic) would see those categories default to `EXPENSE`. How to solve this?.

